        "page_2": {
            "all_text_blocks": [
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        74.06400299072266,
                        59.323204040527344,
                        538.5083618164062,
                        71.09760284423828
                    ],
                    "text": "1. Using this drawing\u2019s legend, what is the difference between a supply air diffuser and a supply air"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        89.06400299072266,
                        72.7832260131836,
                        435.8456726074219,
                        84.55762481689453
                    ],
                    "text": "swirl diffuser, and how many of each appear on the Upper Ground layout?"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        74.06400299072266,
                        91.2632064819336,
                        503.396240234375,
                        103.03760528564453
                    ],
                    "text": "2. What mechanical equipment is shown across the set (e.g. fan coil units, VRF condenser,"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        89.06400299072266,
                        104.70320892333984,
                        449.1656799316406,
                        116.47760772705078
                    ],
                    "text": "mechanical switchboard, MVHR unit), and on which level does each appear?"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        74.06400299072266,
                        123.18318939208984,
                        383.4056701660156,
                        134.9575958251953
                    ],
                    "text": "3. How many fire dampers are shown on the layouts, and where?"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        74.06400299072266,
                        141.66317749023438,
                        539.1100463867188,
                        153.4375762939453
                    ],
                    "text": "4. Decode the abbreviations defined on the cover sheet (e.g. FW, TD, CP, DG, UC) and locate one"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        89.06400299072266,
                        155.22323608398438,
                        278.86566162109375,
                        166.9976348876953
                    ],
                    "text": "example of any one of them on a layout."
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        74.06400299072266,
                        173.70321655273438,
                        513.3546142578125,
                        185.4776153564453
                    ],
                    "text": "5. Distinguish refrigerant pipework from condensate pipework using the pipework legend, and"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        89.06400299072266,
                        187.14321899414062,
                        215.14569091796875,
                        198.91761779785156
                    ],
                    "text": "describe where each runs."
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        66.02400207519531,
                        212.7200164794922,
                        155.39599609375,
                        226.1000213623047
                    ],
                    "text": "What to deliver"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        77.06400299072266,
                        231.90322875976562,
                        537.3380737304688,
                        243.67762756347656
                    ],
                    "text": "\u2013 A runnable application \u2014 we should be able to start it locally from your README with a single"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        89.06400299072266,
                        245.49319458007812,
                        201.7056884765625,
                        257.267578125
                    ],
                    "text": "documented command."
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        77.06400299072266,
                        263.4931945800781,
                        437.5256652832031,
                        275.267578125
                    ],
                    "text": "\u2013 The source repository \u2014 your code, with the README described above."
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        77.06400299072266,
                        281.3731994628906,
                        536.152587890625,
                        293.1475830078125
                    ],
                    "text": "\u2013 A decision log (approximately two pages). Covering what you built and what you deliberately"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        89.06400299072266,
                        294.9331970214844,
                        545.5517578125,
                        333.58758544921875
                    ],
                    "text": "left out; the main technical choices and your reasons for them; where the system is unreliable and \nhow you established that; and how you would extend the approach to large, multi-sheet drawing \nsets. Prose is sufficient; there is no need to build this part."
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        77.06400299072266,
                        339.8132019042969,
                        516.9956665039062,
                        351.58758544921875
                    ],
                    "text": "\u2013 A 3\u20135 minute screen recording demonstrating two or three of these questions end to end."
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        66.02400207519531,
                        365.510009765625,
                        124.07599639892578,
                        378.8899841308594
                    ],
                    "text": "Guidance"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        77.06400299072266,
                        384.6932067871094,
                        520.4824829101562,
                        396.46759033203125
                    ],
                    "text": "\u2013 We would rather see a smaller number of questions answered reliably than all ten attempted"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        89.06400299072266,
                        398.1332092285156,
                        538.67724609375,
                        423.3675842285156
                    ],
                    "text": "superficially. Prioritise accordingly, and record in your decision log what you chose not to do and \nwhy."
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        77.06400299072266,
                        429.59320068359375,
                        535.9739379882812,
                        441.3675842285156
                    ],
                    "text": "\u2013 You may use AI coding tools such as Claude Code, Cursor, or Copilot, and we assume you will."
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        89.06400299072266,
                        443.033203125,
                        539.59619140625,
                        468.3675842285156
                    ],
                    "text": "We assess how you direct these tools and the reasoning behind your decisions, not whether you \nwrote every line by hand."
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        77.06400299072266,
                        474.59320068359375,
                        548.498046875,
                        486.3675842285156
                    ],
                    "text": "\u2013 There is no single correct model or architecture. We are interested in your reasoning, including the"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        89.06400299072266,
                        488.033203125,
                        288.2256774902344,
                        499.8075866699219
                    ],
                    "text": "alternatives you considered and set aside."
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        66.02400207519531,
                        513.72998046875,
                        161.39599609375,
                        527.1099853515625
                    ],
                    "text": "What we assess"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        66.02400207519531,
                        532.7931518554688,
                        542.3510131835938,
                        586.2376098632812
                    ],
                    "text": "We are assessing four things: your ability to work independently, to scope the problem sensibly, to \ndeliver an application that runs, and to reason clearly about where a VLM-based system performs well \nand where it fails. A limited solution accompanied by an accurate account of its failure modes is \nstronger than an ambitious one presented as complete."
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        66.02400207519531,
                        600.52001953125,
                        134.03599548339844,
                        613.9000244140625
                    ],
                    "text": "The debrief"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        66.02400207519531,
                        619.7031860351562,
                        543.642333984375,
                        673.1176147460938
                    ],
                    "text": "After submission, you will have a short debrief with Vivek, our founder, to review your solution: the \ndecisions you made, what you would change given more time, and a small live modification to the \nrunning application. Please be prepared to navigate and explain your own code during this session, as \nthis matters more to us than the finish of the submission."
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        66.02400207519531,
                        687.39599609375,
                        137.39599609375,
                        700.7760009765625
                    ],
                    "text": "Submission"
                },
                {
                    "bbox": [
                        66.02400207519531,
                        706.6422119140625,
                        535.1798706054688,
                        731.0736083984375
                    ],
                    "text": "Please send the repository link, decision log, and recording to vivek@encraft.ai by 5th June 2026 midnight \n(end of day). If anything in this brief is unclear, you are welcome to ask."
                }
            ],
